---
/**
 * Creature license page — the plain-language grant that submitters agree to
 * when they tick the license checkbox on /creatures/submit. Kept as a
 * standalone page so we can bump `license_version` without restyling the
 * form. The version string below must match what the submit form sends.
 */
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

export const LICENSE_VERSION = 'v1-2026-04';
---

<Base
  title="Creature license"
  description="The simple rules for sharing a creature with Matlu."
>
  <h1>Sharing your creature with Matlu</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Before you send us your creature, please read this with a grown-up.
    It explains what happens to your drawing and your story after you
    send them in.
  </p>

  <section class="grant">
    <h2>By submitting your creature, you're saying&hellip;</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>You made it yourself.</strong>
        The drawing and the description are your own work. You're not
        copying someone else's art or characters.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You're OK with us using it.</strong>
        You give Matlu permission to:
        <ul>
          <li>Show your creature on the Matlu wiki and in the game.</li>
          <li>
            Put your creature into the game as a character. We might
            change how it looks or acts a bit so it fits with the
            other creatures.
          </li>
          <li>Share it on social media and in videos about Matlu.</li>
          <li>
            Keep using it forever, even if you later change your mind.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>This is a hobby project &mdash; no payment.</strong>
        We're not going to pay you for your creature.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You can still use your own creature.</strong>
        You keep the right to use your own drawing for anything else
        you want. We just also get to use it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Credits.</strong>
        If you fill in <em>Your name</em> on the form, we'll add you
        to the Matlu credits page &mdash; unless you uncheck the
        <em>Include my name in the credits</em> box.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Grown-ups need to say yes too.</strong>
        If you're under 18, a parent or guardian needs to read this
        with you and agree.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p class="kicker">
      If any of this doesn't feel right, please don't submit. You can
      still play the game and look at the creatures other kids have made.
    </p>

    <p class="version">License version <code>{LICENSE_VERSION}</code></p>
  </section>

  <p class="back">
    <a href="/creatures/submit">&larr; Back to the creature form</a>
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead { color: var(--text-dim); max-width: 620px; margin: 0.5rem 0 2rem; }

  .grant {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .grant h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  .grant ol { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .grant ol > li { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .grant ol > li ul { margin-top: 0.35rem; }
  .grant ol > li ul > li { margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }

  .kicker {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.15rem 0 0.15rem 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .version { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }

  .back { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
</style>
